x4freetext: SECTIONS FROM INELASTIC NEUTRON SCATTERING IN SOME
CHROMIUM AND NICKEL ISOTOPES BETWEEN 0.5 AND 10 MEV-
THE KARLSRUHE CYCLOTRON GAVE 45 MEV DEUTERONS.
PULSED NEUTRON BEAM WAS FURNISHED BY BOMBARDING
A THICK NATURAL URANIUM TARGET WITH THE DEUTERONS,
USING THE REACTION U(D,XN).NEUTRONS HAS A CONTINUOUS
SPECTRUM OF ENERGIES IN THE RANGE 0.5 TO 30 MEV.THE
PULSE WIDTH WAS 2NSEC,AND THE PULSE RECURRENCE
.A RING-SHAPED SCATTERING SAMPLE WAS PLACED AT A
DISTANCE OF 57.9 M FROM THE NEUTRON SOURCE,HAVING
AN INNER DIAMETER OF 120 MM,AN OUTER DIAMETER OF
254 MM AND A THICKNESS OF 6.0 AND 5.5 MM FOR
NATURAL CR (99.89 PC CHEMICAL PURITY) AND NI (99.98 PC
THE EXPERIMENTAL DEVICE CONSISTING OF A GAMMA
RAY SPECTROMETER USED IN CONJONCTION WITH THE
KARLSRUHE FAST NEUTRON TIME OF FLIGHT SPECTROMETER
SCINTILLATION COUNTER USED TO MEASURE THE
NEUTRON FLUX DURING THE SAMPLE OUT PERIODS.
